Package komposten.leapjna.leapc.util

Class ArrayPointer<T extends com.sun.jna.Structure>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sun.jna.Pointer
      • com.sun.jna.Memory
        • komposten.leapjna.leapc.util.ArrayPointer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The structure type contained in the array.
    public class ArrayPointer<T extends com.sun.jna.Structure>
extends com.sun.jna.Memory

    A pointer to a memory block containing one or more instances of a constant-size Structure.

    Use getElement(int) or getElements(Structure[]) to access the array data.
    Use setElement(int, Structure) or setElements(Structure[], int) to write data to the array.

    In order for this class to work properly the structure class stored by this array must have a public no-arg constructor, a public constructor taking a single Pointer as argument, and a constant size.

    • Method Detail

      • empty

        public static <T extends com.sun.jna.Structure> ArrayPointer<T> empty​(Class<T> clazz,
                                                                      int arraySize)

        Creates an empty ArrayPointer based on the provided type and array size.

        Note: All elements will be assumed to have the same size, calculated using Structure.size()!

        Use getElement(int) or getElements(Structure[]) to access the array data.
        Use setElement(int, Structure) or setElements(Structure[], int) to write data to the array.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The structure type the array should store.
        Parameters:
        clazz - The type to store in the array.
        arraySize - The number of elements to allocate space for.
        Returns:
        An ArrayPointer of the specified size pointing to an "empty" memory block.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the specified type has no public no-arg constructor, if its size is zero, or if its size cannot be determined.

      • fromArray

        public static <T extends com.sun.jna.Structure> ArrayPointer<T> fromArray​(T[] values)

        Creates an ArrayPointer based on the provided array. The elements in the provided array will be copied from native memory, so ensure that they have been written before calling this method.

        Since all elements are stored in a contiguous memory block, null elements will be replaced by "empty" elements (all values set to 0).

        Note: All elements will be assumed to have the same size, calculated using Structure.size() on the first element in values!

        Use getElement(int) or getElements(Structure[]) to access the array data.
        Use setElement(int, Structure) or setElements(Structure[], int) to write data to the array.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The structure type the array should store.
        Parameters:
        values - The elements to store in the array.
        Returns:
        An ArrayPointer containing copies of the provided values.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If values is zero-length.
        NullPointerException - If all of the elements in values is null.

      • fromPointer

        public static <T extends com.sun.jna.Structure> ArrayPointer<T> fromPointer​(com.sun.jna.Pointer pointer,
                                                                            Class<T> clazz,
                                                                            int arraySize)

        Creates an ArrayPointer based on the provided pointer, element type and array size.

        Note: All elements will be assumed to have the same size, calculated using Structure.size()!

        Note: This instance is not registered in Memory.allocatedMemory and will therefore not be disposed by Memory.disposeAll(). It will still be disposed when GC'd, though.

        Use getElement(int) or getElements(Structure[]) to access the array data.
        Use setElement(int, Structure) or setElements(Structure[], int) to write data to the array.

        Type Parameters:
        T - The structure type the array should store.
        Parameters:
        pointer - A pointer to the memory block of an existing array of clazz structs.
        clazz - The type of the structs stored in the array.
        arraySize - The number of elements in the array.
        Returns:
        An ArrayPointer of the specified size pointing to the provided memory block.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the specified type has no public no-arg constructor.

      • setElement

        public void setElement​(int index,
                       T value)

        Updates a single element in the array referenced by this object. The element will be copied from native memory, so ensure that it has been written before calling this method.

        Note: If value is null, the memory block at the given index will only be cleared with zeros. This means that calling getElement on that index will return an "empty" structure (all values are 0) rather than null.

        Parameters:
        index - The array index of the element to update.
        value - The new value. May be null.
        Throws:
        ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the index is negative, or greater than or equal to getArraySize().

      • setElements

        public void setElements​(T[] source,
                        int destOffset)

        Copies the provided elements into the array referenced by this object. The provided elements will be copied from native memory, so ensure that they have been written before calling this method.

        Note: If any of the values are null, the memory block at those indices will only be cleared with zeros. This means that calling getElement on those indices will return "empty" structures (all values are 0) rather than null.

        Parameters:
        source - The new elements. May contain null values.
        destOffset - The array index to copy the elements to.
        Throws:
        ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the offset is negative or the offset plus the array size is larger than getArraySize().

      • setElements

        public void setElements​(T[] source,
                        int sourceOffset,
                        int destOffset,
                        int count)

        Copies the provided elements into the array referenced by this object. The provided elements will be copied from native memory, so ensure that they have been written before calling this method.

        Note: If any of the values are null, the memory block at those indices will only be cleared with zeros. This means that calling getElement on those indices will return "empty" structures (all values are 0) rather than null.

        Parameters:
        source - The source array to copy elements from.
        sourceOffset - The offset into source to start copying from.
        destOffset - The offset into this ArrayPointer to copy to.
        count - The number of objects to copy.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - If source is null.
        IllegalArgumentException - If count is negative.
        ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - If the specified source or destination range exceeds the source or destination bounds.

      • equals

        public boolean equals​(Object other)

        Checks whether this ArrayPointer is equal to another object. other is considered equal if and only if it is an ArrayPointer with the same array size, element size and element type, and its elements are equal to the elements in this ArrayPointer.

        Element equality is tested using the elements' equals() methods.

        Use shallowEquals(Object) instead if you want to compare the native peer values (i.e. memory addresses) instead of the actual elements.

        Overrides:
        equals in class com.sun.jna.Pointer

      • shallowEquals

        public boolean shallowEquals​(Object other)

        Checks whether this ArrayPointer is "shallowly" equal to another object. other is considered "shallowly" equal if and only if it is an ArrayPointer with the same array size, element size, element type and native peer value.

        Parameters:
        other - The reference object with which to compare.
        Returns:
        true if this object is the same as the other object; false otherwise.
